<p>President Trump said he would impose an additional 100% tariff on Chinese imports starting November 1 or sooner, and indicated the measures would include export controls on software [ft.com#1][npr.org#1][euronews.com#1][mercopress.com#1]. The threat follows Beijing’s new global restrictions on the use of rare earth minerals, key inputs for U.S. makers of chips and batteries [nytimes.com#1][france24.com#1]. The surcharge would be on top of existing tariffs of 30% on Chinese goods, according to reporting from Mercopress [mercopress.com#1]. Outlets noted the proposed tariff rate could approach levels that in April fanned fears of a recession [npr.org#1][euronews.com#1], and France 24 reported he also threatened to cancel a summit with Xi Jinping [france24.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/OkvYepC0i7Vb_UXXXmVWc7yuyFPhm9C6g3xjjkK3X4TwPF42PHjFrib1RzJMXEl99H3IiNpicCEm0QERuNnrP_p4VNdVig8Otg-j2FTNyoWSs6ROe0QmSho8KPmewkyNbT-snbD8tQQVnGynwi2LViVOVSmspcX1MLyqMKLk-l_KkwwrB2BMd2zgokuxIlJUISlDVLffpL_t-MoF1NzqohlZA84' alt='President Trump said proposed tariffs would take effect Nov. 1 and be imposed over and above other tariffs on Chinese exports.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Timing and scope: The President said an additional 100% tariff on Chinese imports would start November 1 or sooner [ft.com#1][npr.org#1][euronews.com#1][mercopress.com#1].</li><li>Tech controls: The package would also include new U.S. export controls on software, according to the Financial Times [ft.com#1].</li><li>Trigger factor: Beijing’s new global curbs on rare earth minerals—vital for chips and batteries—prompted the U.S. move [nytimes.com#1][france24.com#1].</li><li>Tariff stacking: The 100% surcharge would be added on top of existing 30% tariffs on Chinese goods [mercopress.com#1].</li><li>Economic risk: Media noted the rates could near levels that in April stirred recession fears [npr.org#1][euronews.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Trump: He said the tariffs would take effect November 1 or sooner and that measures would include export controls on software. (<a href='https://www.ft.com/content/328e3195-909a-45fb-b118-9dafbd41262b'>Financial Times</a>)</li><li>Euronews: It noted the proposed rate could approach levels that earlier this year fanned fears of a global recession. (<a href='http://www.euronews.com/2025/10/11/trump-threatens-new-100-tariff-on-chinese-imports-starting-1-november-or-sooner'>Euronews</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/328e3195-909a-45fb-b118-9dafbd41262b'>Donald Trump threatens extra 100% tariff as he retaliates against China</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/11/g-s1-93113/trump-threatens-100-tariff-chinese-imports'>Trump threatens tech export limits, new 100% tariff on Chinese imports</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/10/us/politics/trump-xi-china-tariffs-rare-earth.html'>Trump Threatens 100% Tariffs on Chinese Goods</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/worldnews/comments/1o414qm/trump_announces_extra_100_tariff_on_chinese_goods/'>Trump announces extra 100% tariff on Chinese goods starting next month</a> - reddit.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251011-trump-announces-additional-100-percent-tariff-on-chinese-imports'>Trump announces additional 100 percent tariff on Chinese imports</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://en.mercopress.com/2025/10/11/trump-announces-additional-tariffs-on-chinese-products'>Trump announces additional tariffs on Chinese products</a> - mercopress.com</li><li><a href='http://www.euronews.com/2025/10/11/trump-threatens-new-100-tariff-on-chinese-imports-starting-1-november-or-sooner'>Trump threatens new 100% tariff on Chinese imports starting 1 November or sooner</a> - euronews.com</li></ul>